Email From: Honolulu County Steve Lipscomb 

Aloha Honolulu County Patriots,

Today we received a suspicious email at our OahuGOP info@oahugop.com email address, claiming to be from Republican National Committee (RNC) legal department. Attached to the email was a “Cease & Desist” letter addressed to Past Chair Brett Kulbis.

As you know, scam emails are the preferred method for nefarious groups and individuals to gain access to our personal information or trick us into doing something bogus. Some of the easiest ways to expose these scams is by scrutinizing the contents.

In this case there are several inconsistencies about this email and attachment:

   1.  The email was received today at 9:19 am, which is 3:19 pm in Washington DC where the RNC HQ is located. If this email was legit, it would have been sent earlier in the week so that inquiries could be made immediately and not wait over a weekend. This is a similar tactic email scammers often use.

   2.  The cease and desist letter is addressed to past chair Kulbis; and the supporting document only shows the footer of our website, but if it was really legit the individual would have seen at the top of the website the County election announcement and the email would have been addressed to me.  Leadership of the Honolulu County Republican Party was formally transitioned to new officers at the official county convention several weeks ago, pursuant to state and county GOP rules.  Any serious attorney would have performed the needed due diligence and known this.  I’ve reached out to “Ms. McGuire” of the “RNC” to confirm or rebut the legitimacy of this email. I’m still awaiting her response.

   3.  The spoof email erroneously suggests that legitimately formed and duly elected county GOP organizations like ours have no legitimate rights for party branding and/or communication like thousands of county parties across the nation.  Hence, the spoof message assumes we will ignore the infinite number of legitimate Republican county party websites and social media accounts just like ours which have been in operation for years and years.  Obviously, a nefarious actor wishes to silence your county leadership team.

   4.  It is widely known that the RNC does not get involved at the County levels unless a State Party has requested their assistance. I’ve reached out to Chair Garcia to see if he knows about this. I’m still awaiting his response.

   5.  Neither the Kauai, Maui, East Hawaii, nor West Hawaii county party organizations have received a similar cease & desist letter.

   6.  As mentioned above, nationally there are hundreds of counties that use “GOP” in their website and social media title and descriptions. Just looking at one state: California you have Sacramento GOP: “SacCountyGOP” Home Page - Sacramento County Republican Party (saccountygop.com); and Orange County: Republican Party of Orange County - Leadership (ocgop.org). I’ve reached out to some other county parties and are awaiting their responses.

While we continue to investigate this potential scam email, I wanted to make sure you’re aware should you receive something similarly suspect and misleading. If you do, please forward it to me ASAP at steve.lipscomb@outlook.com.

Your county leadership team is always on the lookout for spoofs and scams which seek to hijack our movement and undermine our mission. Please know that we will defend our party against those who seek to interfere with our organization, our messaging, our branding, and our determination to turn Hawai`i RED!

All the Best,
Steve
